  "text": "14 In our study, amenorrhea was more common in the TCRE group than in LNG-IUS at 12 months posttreatment (44.7% vs 11.1% respectively) and spotting was more common in LNG-IUS group (38% vs 12%). In Hidalgo et al, 44% of the women who had LNG-IUS inserted reported amenorrhea at the 6th month of use. This rate maintained stability in 50% of these women after 12 and 24 months of use and spotting was present in 25% of the users at 6 months, decreasing to 11% at 24 months. This rate maintained stability at 50% after 12 and 24 months of use. [CITATION_1] Wide dissemination of information on the expected bleeding patterns after LNG-IUS insertion is necessary, so that it can reduce unnecessary, more radical, surgery.",
